sec.p:
One-hundred and twenty-six patients (86%) performed the TUG at the 3-week follow-up with a duration of TUG performance between 11 and 266 s (median 30 s, mean 46 s). Twenty patients (12 LAT, 8 AMIS) could not start or finish the test and entered the analysis with a value set to 300 s:
2 patients had too poor of a performance status to start the test;
2 patients suffered from too much pain to start the test;
2 patients could not move without assistance;
5 patients could not move to a chair;
7 patients could not stand up from a chair; and
2 patients could not walk 3 m.
